<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: PASADENA; 6-DAY DISNEY 
YOUTH SOCCER CUP KICKS OFF ON MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Just as World Cup '94 ends, 6,000 athletes from around the world will arrive 
in Pasadena to play soccer. 
</P>
<P>
 Say what? 
</P>
<P>
 The Disney International Youth Soccer Cup will draw the amateur players, ages 
10 to 19, for a six-day event beginning Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Italy, Brazil, the United States and 13 other countries are sending 6,000 
athletes, or 395 teams, to the cup July 18-24. Each team is divided by age and 
gender, and will have the chance to play at least five games in area fields, 
with the final games to held at Pasadena's Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 Athletes, who started arriving last week, will stay with local families or in 
nearby hotels, said Disney spokesman Rich Bertolucci. "They've already set up 
side games to practice and get used to our climate," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is hosted by the American Youth Soccer Organization, with Disney and 
other sponsors coordinating the registration and recreational activities. 
Opening ceremonies, which are free to the public, will be held in Old Pasadena 
on Monday, with a 7 p.m. parade along Holly Street. 
</P>
</TEXT>
