<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; MAN WOUNDED IN STREET ALTERCATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 19-year-old Ventura man was shot in the arm during an altercation with four 
other teen-agers, Ventura police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 James D. Bolden was treated for the wound at Ventura County Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Lt. Don Arth said a group of youths walking on the sidewalk in the 1600 block 
of Ocean Avenue approached Bolden and a friend, who were standing on a porch 
about 10:24 p.m. Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 "Apparently there was some conversation," Arth said. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the youths pulled out a pistol and shot several rounds at Bolden and 
his friend, striking Bolden in the arm. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects fled in a silver Toyota and have not been apprehended. But Arth 
said police found a stolen vehicle matching the description of their car at 
Olive and Center streets. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
