<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS : CONEJO VALLEY; COLLECTIONS SOUGHT TO RESTOCK FOOD 
BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To restock Manna, the local food bank, the Conejo Valley Board of Realtors 
will hold a "Super Saturday" grocery collection outside seven local 
supermarkets today. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers will stand outside the markets urging shoppers to purchase a few 
extra items to donate to Manna.The food bank will accept canned goods, diapers, 
paper supplies and groceries. Last year, a similar event collected $7,000 worth 
of food. 
</P>
<P>
 "People give a lot around Christmas, but in the summer Manna doesn't have much 
food, so we're trying to stock their shelves," organizer Steve Perry said. 
</P>
<P>
 To further bolster Manna, the real estate agents will hold a charity fashion 
show at Charley Brown's restaurant on Moorpark Road later this month. Tickets 
to the show, scheduled for July 28th at 6 p.m., cost $15. For more information, 
call Perry at 529-0836. 
</P>
<P>
 The grocery stores participating in today's food drive are: Vons markets on 
Avenida de los Arboles, Agoura Road and Kanan Road; Ralphs market on Moorpark 
Road; Lucky market on Newbury Road, Pavilions in North Ranch; and Hughes Market 
on Ventu Park Road. STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</TEXT>
