<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 6-year-old Moorpark boy was slightly injured Friday night when he was hit by 
a car driven by a suspected drunk driver, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher Lopez suffered minor injuries after he stepped onto 2nd Street 
near Moorpark Avenue about 7:15 p.m. and was hit by a car traveling westbound 
on 2nd, according to Ventura County Sheriff's Sgt. Keith Parks. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy was taken to Simi Valley Hospital, where he was treated for a bump on 
his head and minor cuts and bruises, authorities said. A hospital official said 
he would probably be released late Friday. 
