<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAIWAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was so glad to read your editorial "Giving Taiwanese an Even Break" (July 
10).Finally, someone is bringing justice to an island of hard-working people! 
</P>
<P>
 Yes, when Taiwan was abandoned by its biggest ally, Uncle Sam, in 1979, people 
there were scared. However, the Taiwanese stood on their own feet, worked hard, 
and eventually became a major economic force. As a Chinese American born in 
Taiwan, I am extremely proud of Taiwan's accomplishments. However, they have 
been a voiceless group. Politically and culturally, they have been isolated 
from the rest of the world.  
</P>
<P>
 Give Taiwan something back. Help Taiwan reach the next level of excellence! 
</P>
<P>
 TAMMY MEI-TAN CHANG 
</P>
<P>
 West Covina 
