EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; FAIR PROCEEDS TO AID PROJECT FOR DISABLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For those who like to do their holiday shopping early, there is the upcoming 
"Christmas in July" gift fair sponsored by the Independent Living Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty-five local crafts people will tout their wares -- from handmade dolls 
to lamps -- at the center July 30 and 31 to raise funds for a pre-employment 
program for people with severe disabilities, according to community education 
coordinator Sherman Pearl. 
</P>
<P>
 The pre-employment program provides training in office, homemaking and 
horticultural skills for people with physical, developmental and sensory 
disabilities, as well as for survivors of traumatic brain injuries.  
</P>
<P>
 Recently, the program's participants joined with the Urban Greening Program of 
the U.S. Forestry Service to plant greenery in Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 Pearl said he hopes the crafts fair will raise about $5,000 for the program. 
</P>
<P>
 Christmas in July will take place at 14151 Haynes St., Van Nuys. It will begin 
at 10 a.m. both days. For more information, call (818) 785-6934. MAKI BECKER 
