<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 MEN FACE HAZARDOUS WASTE CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men were charged Friday with abandoning hazardous waste in Sun Valley, the 
Los Angeles city attorney's office reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Jafar Rassouli, 45, of Canoga Park and Hamid Nadjafi, 35, of Reseda are 
accused of abandoning six 55-gallon drums of highly flammable waste paint at 
their former business, Best Auto Body, on Sherman Way, the city attorney's 
office said. 
</P>
<P>
 They were each charged with one count of illegally disposing of hazardous 
waste and six counts of violating state regulations regarding the handling of 
hazardous materials, the statement said. 
</P>
<P>
 The drums were discovered last year when a new owner moved in, according to 
Deputy City Atty. Brooke White.  
</P>
<P>
 The men are scheduled to be arraigned Aug. 11 in Los Angeles Municipal Court. 
If convicted, they could be sentenced to two years in jail and fined more than 
$100,000. 
</P>
