<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIME-SHARE FIRM IN NEWPORT PURCHASED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MPTV Inc. in Minneapolis said Friday that it has bought Reefshare Ltd., a 
vacation time-share company, for an undisclosed price.Reefshare owns the right 
to purchase dwelling units and sell time-shares in Kona Reef Condominiums in 
Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
 MPTV also picked up $300,000 in accounts receivable owed to Reefshare, which 
is based in Newport Beach. It said it hopes to garner revenue of $90 million in 
the next 24 months from sales of 6,500 unit-weeks at the Kona Reef. 
</P>
