<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The monthlong World Cup soccer tournament comes to a climax Sunday when Brazil 
and Italy play for the championship at the Rose Bowl, beginning at 12:30 p.m. 
on ABC (Channels 7, 3, 10 and 42). 
</P>
<P>
 Tonight at 6 on cable's TNT, Grammy winner Toni Braxton, Andrew Shue ("Melrose 
Place"), CBS' Pat O'Brien, Sinbad and All-4-One will appear on "Hollywood 
Backstage at the World Cup," broadcast live from the back lot of Paramount 
