ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; COUNCIL WILL REVIEW CITY BUDGET TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Council members will review the city's $37.3-million budget with department 
heads in an all-day session today. 
</P>
<P>
 The city projects deficits of $406,000 in the general fund and $654,000 in the 
water fund, Finance Director Greg Beaubien said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're not suggesting any cuts, but we're also not adding any new programs," 
he said. "We're trying to maintain services at their present levels." 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will begin at 8 a.m. in the council chambers at 6650 Beach Blvd., 
and will run for most of the day, Beaubien said. 
</P>
<P>
 He noted that the negotiations with city employees are ongoing and the budget 
may have to be amended. Budget projections call for no pay increases. 
</P>
<P>
 Beaubien attributed some of the deficits to a slight decrease in revenue for 
the general fund, which is down by just under $300,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Funds will be taken out of the city's reserve, which now totals about $3.1 
million, Beaubien said. LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
