<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; RED CROSS WORRIED OVER BLOOD SHORTAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Red Cross officials are urging healthy people to donate blood to offset an 
unusually early summer blood shortage. 
</P>
<P>
 The nationwide shortage is especially worrisome in Southern California because 
blood has to be imported here from throughout the country during normal times. 
</P>
<P>
 Unless donors step forward, the blood supply may fall below emergency levels, 
forcing patients to delay elective surgeries, said spokeswoman Judy Iannaccone. 
</P>
<P>
 Normally, blood shortages are rare before Labor Day. 
</P>
<P>
 This year blood supplies have been chronically low in part because severe 
weather in the midwest and eastern portions of the country during the winter 
hampered blood collection efforts, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Furthermore, about half of the people who schedule appointments to donate 
blood fail to show up. If all the people who scheduled appointments followed 
through, the crisis would be over, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Potential donors should call (800) 974-2113 to make an appointment. JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
