<P>
 Sure, all of the Saudi Arabians earned Mercedes-Benzes for qualifying, but 
there is also some incentive for Italy. 
</P>
<P>
 Bugatti, the Italian super-car manufacturer, announced Friday it will present 
the most valuable player of its country's national soccer team with a ritzy 
EB110 GT. There is only one condition: Italy must beat Brazil in Sunday's 
final. 
</P>
<P>
 Powered by a 12-cylinder, 60-valve, quad-turbo engine of 3.5 liters (we 
couldn't make it up), this special gift will be available for an estimated 
$335,000 to the U.S. public this fall. It is capable of speeds in excess of 200 
m.p.h and the U.S. version will have up to 600 horsepower. 
