<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FINALS; SPOTLIGHT; MORE CLUCK FOR BUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What do you say to a 10-foot tall chicken? 
</P>
<P>
 Most folks who encountered Alcedes Andrade outside the Rose Bowl on Wednesday 
didn't say anything.They just posed for pictures with the 45-year-old 
Brazilian. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is my fifth World Cup. I always go as something different," said 
Andrade, who went to Mexico in 1986 dressed as a parakeet. "They wouldn't let 
me in (to the game) in San Francisco." 
</P>
<P>
 Why would anyone wear a hot, heavy costume dotted with the green and yellow of 
the Brazilian team? 
</P>
<P>
 To Andrade, it made perfect sense. "To gain attention of the entire world for 
Brazil," he said. HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
