<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD PARK; COOL AIR SETS STAKES RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cool Air left eight rivals feeling her draft as she posted a stakes record 
time of 1:01 3/5 for 5 1/2 furlongs on the turf in capturing Friday night's 
$155,600 Budweiser Breeders' Cup at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Cool Air, the only filly in the field of eight sprinters, surged under jockey 
Chris Antley in the final furlong as she drew away to win by 2 1/2 lengths over 
D'Hallevant. Bahatur finished third. 
</P>
<P>
 The winner's share of $88,100 boosted Cool Air's earnings to $448,503. 
</P>
<P>
 Cool Air, trained by Gary Jones and a winner of 12 of 26 lifetime starts, paid 
$4.20 to win as the 6-5 betting choice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071694-0241 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 061252 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
July 16, 1994, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
