<HEADLINE>
<P>
36 APPLY TO BE TITAN ATHLETIC DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LON EUBANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thirty-six candidates have applied for the vacant Cal State Fullerton athletic 
director position. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for receiving applications for "full consideration" was Friday, 
according to Alan Saltzstein, search committee chairman. Saltzstein said 
committee members will review candidates individually next week, and the 
committee will meet again later in the month. 
</P>
<P>
 Saltzstein said the committee will select "four to six" candidates for the 
position to recommend to school president Milton A. Gordon. Saltzstein said the 
committee will interview each of these candidates in late August.  
</P>
<P>
 The school seeks to replace Bill Shumard, who resigned in May and later became 
an assistant athletic director at Long Beach State, his alma mater. LON EUBANKS 
</P>
